---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="SECTOR 404 — Unauthorized Access Point"
  description="Your route resolved when it should have failed. Choose an access route: artifacts, signals or archive."
>
  <section class="breach-home hero portal hero-image" data-breach-home>
    <div class="breach-boot" data-breach-boot aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="breach-boot__panel">
        <p>RPI BLACK CHANNEL / RECOVERED HANDSHAKE</p>
        <span data-breach-line></span>
        <span data-breach-line></span>
        <span data-breach-line></span>
        <span data-breach-line></span>
        <span data-breach-line></span>
        <span data-breach-line></span>
        <span data-breach-line></span>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="breach-cursor" data-breach-cursor aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="breach-vault" aria-hidden="true">
      <span class="vault-ring r1"></span>
      <span class="vault-ring r2"></span>
      <span class="vault-ring r3"></span>
      <span class="vault-core"></span>
    </div>
    <div class="breach-frame breach-frame--alive" aria-hidden="true">
      <span>RPI/CCTV-404</span>
      <span>LIVE FEED DEGRADED</span>
      <span>NO OFFICIAL RECORD</span>
      <span>CAMERA 09 SEES A DOOR</span>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-copy breach-hero-copy">
      <p class="terminal-label breach-readout" data-breach-readout>route anomaly confirmed</p>
      <h1 class="hero-title sector-red breach-title" data-text="SECTOR"><span class="sector-word">SECTOR</span><br /><span class="sector-code">404</span></h1>
      <p class="lead breach-lead">You were not invited. The corridor opened anyway. SECTOR 404 is a leak: artifacts, infected signals and recovered files from a department RACHELL POST INDUSTRIES denies exists.</p>
      <div class="hero-actions breach-actions">
        <a class="button primary breach-enter" href="#access-routes-title" data-breach-enter>Begin breach</a>
        <a class="button" href="works/">View Artifacts</a>
        <a class="button" href="world/">Open Archive</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <aside class="access-console compact breach-console-live" aria-label="Unauthorized access console">
      <div><span>access route</span><strong>misdirected / open</strong></div>
      <div><span>public rooms</span><strong>3 visible</strong></div>
      <div><span>handler</span><strong>echo // unresolved</strong></div>
      <div><span>warning</span><strong>clean surfaces lie</strong></div>
    </aside>

    <div class="biometric-ghost biometric-ghost--home" aria-label="Recovered biometric trace">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="assets/sector404/sector-404-biometric-trace-poster.jpg">
        <source src="assets/sector404/sector-404-biometric-trace-clean.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
      <span>RPI BIOMETRIC TRACE / SOURCE DEGRADED</span>
    </div>

    <div class="breach-specimens" aria-hidden="true">
      <figure class="breach-specimen specimen-emanu"><img src="assets/sector404/works/emanu/emanu-01-front.jpg" alt="" loading="eager" /></figure>
      <figure class="breach-specimen specimen-cyber"><img src="assets/sector404/works/cyberhead/cyberhead-09-front-full.jpg" alt="" loading="eager" /></figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="status-strip breach-status-strip" aria-label="Sector status">
    <div><span>Artifacts</span><strong>Physical evidence</strong></div>
    <div><span>Signals</span><strong>Transmissions / drops</strong></div>
    <div><span>Archive</span><strong>Files / world / logs</strong></div>
    <div><span>RPI position</span><strong>Deny access</strong></div>
  </section>

  <section class="section access-routes" aria-labelledby="access-routes-title">
    <div class="section-head clean-head">
      <div>
        <p class="kicker">Choose access route</p>
        <h2 id="access-routes-title">Three doors opened by a failed denial layer.</h2>
      </div>
      <p class="muted">Do not browse this place. Handle it. Each door is a different kind of contamination.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="route-grid breach-route-grid">
      <article class="route-card primary-route surface-card surface-scrap" data-code="ART_404" data-breach-route="artifact manifest unlocked / object memory active">
        <a href="works/">
          <span class="route-number">01</span>
          <span class="kicker">ARTIFACTS</span>
          <h2>Objects that survived their owners.</h2>
          <p class="muted">Sold works and recovered sculpture files. Physical evidence from the error, still warm in the archive.</p>
          <b>Open manifest →</b>
        </a>
      </article>
      <article class="route-card surface-card surface-biometric" data-code="SIG_001" data-breach-route="signal corridor exposed / audio residue moving">
        <a href="signals/">
          <span class="route-number">02</span>
          <span class="kicker">SIGNALS</span>
          <h2>Transmissions that behave like wounds.</h2>
          <p class="muted">PRIEST is the first infected signal, not the whole system. Music, cards and future drops enter here.</p>
          <b>Follow signal →</b>
        </a>
      </article>
      <article class="route-card surface-card surface-dump" data-code="ARC_RPI" data-breach-route="archive door unstable / julian trace found">
        <a href="world/">
          <span class="route-number">03</span>
          <span class="kicker">ARCHIVE</span>
          <h2>The company record and the body beneath it.</h2>
          <p class="muted">RPI, Julian, entities and story fragments. The world layer below the public lie.</p>
          <b>Enter archive →</b>
        </a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section portal-grid intro-split breach-intro-split">
    <article class="panel archive-room photo-room breach-room">
      <div class="archive-caption">
        <p class="kicker">Unmarked file vault</p>
        <h2>Not a shop. A leak with a pulse.</h2>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article class="panel copy-block breach-copy-panel">
      <p class="kicker">RACHELL POST INDUSTRIES denies all association</p>
      <div class="rpi-stamp" aria-label="RACHELL POST INDUSTRIES mark">
        <img src="assets/sector404/rpi-logo.svg" alt="RACHELL POST INDUSTRIES" />
      </div>
      <p>RPI builds sealed futures: body systems, synthetic parts, robotics, weapons, security architecture and industrial prototypes.</p>
      <p>SECTOR 404 is the part of the building that appears only after the cameras disagree. A corridor with no floor plan. A manifest nobody signed.</p>
      <p class="rule">The corporation manufactures the future. Sector 404 shows what falls through the cracks.</p>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section portal-grid evidence-section breach-evidence-section">
    <article class="panel breach-protocol-panel">
      <p class="kicker">Public handling protocol</p>
      <h2>Nothing is presented cleanly here.</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="margin-top:1rem">Artifacts should feel documented rather than displayed. Signals should feel intercepted rather than promoted. Archive files should feel recovered rather than explained.</p>
      <div class="manifest-list">
        <div class="manifest-item"><span>ART</span><b>OBJECTS</b><span>manifest</span></div>
        <div class="manifest-item"><span>SIG</span><b>PRIEST / DROPS</b><span>transmission</span></div>
        <div class="manifest-item"><span>ARC</span><b>RPI / JULIAN</b><span>files</span></div>
      </div>
    </article>
    <article class="evidence-table photo-table breach-evidence-table" aria-label="Artifact evidence table">
      <div class="evidence-card c1" data-title="ARTIFACT"></div>
      <div class="evidence-card c2" data-title="SIGNAL"></div>
      <div class="evidence-card c3" data-title="ARCHIVE"></div>
      <div class="chip a"></div>
      <div class="chip b"></div>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
